<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM3.1.11">
<l>karār mēṉi niṟattem pirāṉaik kaṭikamaḻ pūṅkuḻa lāycci</l>
<l>ārā viṉṉamu tuṇṇat taruvaṉnā ṉammamtā rēṉeṉṟa māṟṟam</l>
<l>pārār tolpuka ḻāṉputu vaimaṉṉaṉ paṭṭar pirāṉcoṉṉa pāṭal</l>
<l>ērā riṉṉicai mālaival lāri ruṭīkē caṉaṭi yārē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master this garland of sweet music full of beauty,</l>
<l rend="indent">[these] verses composed by Lord Scholar, King of Putuvai,</l>
<l rend="indent">he whose ancient fame fills the world,</l>
<l>on the words of the herdess with curling hair [full of] fragrant flowers</l>
<l rend="indent">To our lord with the black-hued body, saying</l>
<l rend="indent">“I will give [you] unlimited sweet nectar to eat,</l>
<l rend="indent">[but] I will not give [you my] breast”,</l>
<l>Are servants of Hṛṣīkeśa.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
